-- L'Occitane International Full-Year Net Income Rises 40% to $100.7 Million
-- Wing-Gar Cheng
-- 2010-06-24T23:59:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/l-occitane-international-full-year-net-income-rises-40-to-100-7-million.html

          
          
             L’Occitane International SA said
profit in the fiscal year ended March 31 rose 40 percent to 81.6
million euros ($100.7 million) and sales gained 14 percent to
612.2 million euros. Earnings per share were 0.064 euros in the
year ended March 31 compared with 0.046 euros a year earlier,
the company said in a statement to Hong Kong’s stock exchange
yesterday.     
